{{Unreferenced|date=April 2015}}
[[File:CBG Centrum voor familiegeschiedenis.svg|thumb|Logo of CBG Centrum voor familiegeschiedenis]]
The '''CBG Centrum voor familiegeschiedenis''' ''(formerly called: Centraal Bureau voor Genealogie)'' (CBG) is the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] research centre for [[genealogy|genealogical]] and [[Heraldry|heraldic]] studies. It is a [[Foundation (nonprofit organization)|non-profit foundation]] that has been founded on May 15, 1945, with the aim of bringing together a number of archive collections and making research of genealogy and related studies easier. The centre is located at the Prins Willem Alexanderhof in [[The Hague]] together with the [[Nationaal Archief|National Archive]].

The CBG publishes many books pertaining to genealogy, for instance the series [[Nederland's Adelsboek]] and [[Nederland's Patriciaat]].

== External links ==
* {{nl}} [http://www.cbg.nl Official website of the Centraal Bureau voor Genealogie]

