1). * {{cite journal |author=Denby, David |authormask=1 |date=January 2, 2012 |title=Battle Stations |department=The Critics. The Current Cinema |journal=The New Yorker |volume=87 |issue=42 |pages=78–79 |url=http://www.newyorker.com/arts/critics/cinema/2012/01/02/120102crci_cinema_denby |<!--accessdate=8 January 2014-->}} Reviews [[Phyllida Lloyd]]'s ''[[The Iron Lady (film)|The Iron Lady]]'' (2011), [[Steven Spielberg]]'s ''[[War Horse (film)|War Horse]]'' (2011) and [[Brad Bird]]'s ''[[Mission: Impossible – Ghost Protocol]]'' (2011). * {{cite journal |author=Denby, David |authormask=1 |date=January 16, 2012 |title=Lost Love |department=The Critics. The Current Cinema |journal=The New Yorker |volume=87 |issue=44 |pages=80–81 |url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2012/01/16/lost–love–3 |<!--accessdate=2014-11-11-->}} Reviews [[Stephen Daldry]]'s ''[[Extremely Loud & Incredibly Close (film)|Extremely Loud & Incredibly Close]]'' (2011) and [[Cameron Crowe]]'s ''[[We Bought a Zoo]]'' (2011). * {{cite journal |author=Denby, David |authormask=1 |date=January 30, 2012 |title=Brotherly Love |department=Goings on About Town. Critic's Notebook |journal=The New Yorker |volume=87 |issue=46 |pages=7}} Reviews [[Gregory La Cava]]'s ''Unfinished Business''. * {{cite journal |author=Denby, David |authormask=1 |date=January 30, 2012 |title=Flesh and Fantasy |department=The Critics. The Current Cinema |journal=The New Yorker |volume=87 |issue=46 |pages=78–79}} [[Frederick Wiseman]]'s ''Crazy Horse'', [[Baltasar Kormákur]]'s ''Contraband'' and [[Steven Soderbergh]]'s ''Haywire''. * {{cite journal |author=Denby, David |authormask=1 |date=February 13–20, 2012 |title=Soldiering On |department=Goings on About Town. Critic's Notebook |journal=The New Yorker |volume=88 |issue=1 |pages=10}} [[William Wellman]]'s ''The Story of G.I. Joe''. * {{cite journal |author=Denby, David |authormask=1 |date=February 13–20, 2012 |title=Powers of Evil |department=The Critics. The Current Cinema |journal