'''''Theaterlexikon der Schweiz''''' ('''TLS''') / '''''Dictionnaire du théâtre en Suisse''''' ('''DTS''') / '''''Dizionario Teatrale Svizzero''''' ('''DTS''') / '''''Lexicon da teater svizzer''''' ('''LTS''') is an encyclopedia about [[theatre]] in [[Switzerland]] published 2005 in 3 volumes. It was developed from 1997 to 2005 by the [[Institute of Theatre Studies]] of the [[University of Berne]].

Its 3600 entries include 3000 biographies and articles about venues, groups, organizations, events and general topics.

Articles are available in German (70%), French (20%), Italian (6%) or Romansh (2%). Romansh articles are translated in German.

The text (without illustrations) was published online in 2012.

